# Lambda Terraform Files — Generated from AWS Account

## What Was Done

Terraformer had a known Windows compatibility bug (`exec: no command`), so we used **AWS CLI** to extract your existing Lambda setup and generated Terraform files from the live data.

## Files Generated

| File | Purpose |
|------|---------|
| [main.tf](file:///c:/Users/lenov/OneDrive%20-%20Appsys%20Global%20Pvt%20Ltd/Desktop/AI%20Agent/Terraforms/Email-Parser-Lambda/main.tf) | IAM roles, 3 Lambda functions, CloudWatch log groups, SQS trigger |
| [variables.tf](file:///c:/Users/lenov/OneDrive%20-%20Appsys%20Global%20Pvt%20Ltd/Desktop/AI%20Agent/Terraforms/Email-Parser-Lambda/variables.tf) | AWS region and account ID variables |
| [versions.tf](file:///c:/Users/lenov/OneDrive%20-%20Appsys%20Global%20Pvt%20Ltd/Desktop/AI%20Agent/Terraforms/Email-Parser-Lambda/versions.tf) | Terraform and AWS provider version constraints |
| [outputs.tf](file:///c:/Users/lenov/OneDrive%20-%20Appsys%20Global%20Pvt%20Ltd/Desktop/AI%20Agent/Terraforms/Email-Parser-Lambda/outputs.tf) | Lambda function and IAM role ARN outputs |

